📄 PROJECT REPORT
✈️ Flight Delay Prediction System
1. Introduction
Flight delays are something most people have experienced while travelling. Sometimes flights get delayed due to bad weather, technical issues, or even because the aircraft arrives late from its previous journey. These delays not only affect passengers but also create problems for airlines in managing their schedules.
In this project, I tried to understand how machine learning can be used to predict whether a flight will be delayed or not. The idea is simple — if we have some basic information about a flight, we can use a model to predict the chances of delay.
This project helped me connect my aerospace background with basic AI/ML concepts in a practical way.

2. Problem Statement
It is not easy to predict flight delays just by guessing, because many factors are involved. Without analyzing data, it becomes difficult to identify patterns.
So, the main problem I worked on is:
Predicting whether a flight will be delayed or not
Using simple data like distance, weather, and departure delay
Applying machine learning to make the prediction.

3. Objectives
The main objectives of this project are:
To understand how machine learning works in real-world problems
To create a dataset related to flight conditions
To train a model that can predict delays
To build a simple system where a user can give inputs and get a prediction

4. Methodology
I completed this project step by step as follows:
4.1 Dataset Creation
Instead of using a ready dataset, I created my own dataset in Excel. I included factors like airline, distance, weather condition, and departure delay. I tried to keep the data realistic so that the model could learn meaningful patterns.
4.2 Data Preparation
After creating the dataset, I saved it in CSV format so it could be used in Python. All the values were numeric because machine learning models cannot directly understand text.
4.3 Model Selection
I selected Logistic Regression for this project. Since the output is either “Delayed” or “Not Delayed”, this model is suitable for classification problems.
4.4 Model Training
Using Python and scikit-learn, I trained the model with the dataset. The model learned how different factors affect flight delays.
4.5 Prediction System
Finally, I created a simple Python program where the user can enter flight details. Based on those inputs, the model predicts whether the flight will be delayed or not.

5. Tools and Technologies Used
Python
Pandas (for handling data)
Scikit-learn (for machine learning model)
Pickle (for saving the trained model)

6. Dataset Description
The dataset includes the following columns:
Airline → represented using numbers
Distance → flight distance in kilometers
Weather → 0 for clear weather, 1 for bad weather
Departure Delay → delay before takeoff in minutes
Delayed → final output (0 = no delay, 1 = delay)

The dataset was manually created, so it is small but structured in a way that reflects real-life situations.

7. Model Description
The model used in this project is Logistic Regression.
It works by analyzing input values and predicting the probability of a delay. Based on this probability, it classifies the result into delayed or not delayed.
I chose this model because it is simple, easy to understand, and suitable for this type of problem.

8. Results and Discussion
After training the model, I tested it with different inputs. The model was able to give reasonable predictions based on the values entered.
For example, when the weather is bad and the departure delay is high, the model predicts that the flight will likely be delayed. This shows that the model is able to capture basic patterns from the dataset.
Even though the dataset is small, the project clearly demonstrates how machine learning works.

